%N A395694 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of labeled 5-multigraphs on n vertices with clique number exactly k.
%C A395694 A 5-multigraph allows edge multiplicities 0..5. Clique number is defined on the underlying simple graph (multiplicity >=1).
%C A395694 Part of the family T_p(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} p^{e(G)}. Row sums give 6^(n*(n-1)/2).
%C A395694 The range p=1..5 covers typical transportation network interlining depths (metro/tram systems). See cross-references for other p values.
%C A395694 Values computed by weighting simple graph enumeration with 5^{e(G)}; verified for n<=6. Extended to n=7,8 via b-file.
%H A395694 Sean A. Irvine, <a href="/A395694/b395694.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..66</a> (terms 1..36 from Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales)
%H A395694 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20004703">Clique-Size Dominance Threshold Distribution...</a>, Zenodo, 2026.
%H A395694 Alejandro Zarzuelo Urdiales, <a href="https://github.com/alejandrozu/Clique-OEIS">Python verification code and Lean 4 formalization</a>, GitHub.
%F A395694 T(n,k) = Sum_{G: omega(G)=k} 5^{e(G)}.
%F A395694 Row sum: Sum_{k=1..n} T(n,k) = 6^(n*(n-1)/2).
